[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I woke up.[l][r]
Chii-chan and I had our last ration...[r]
... and then we went to sleep...[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]I woke up again and wondered how much time has passed. I didn't know.[r]
So I fell back asleep.[l][r]
I've done that thrice over.[l][r]
Shaking my head to clear my vision, I realized... it was snowing.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]Looking up at the sky, I saw the overcast clouds staring right back at us.[r]
Ah, it's noon. Thank goodness. It would've been a little scary if it was nighttime right now.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"... Chi-chan?"[l][r]
I called out to the girl who slept right next to me. She was small, and precious...[l][r]
and she wasn't breathing anymore...[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"H... Hey! Bookworm!"[r]
I tried to tease, hoping it'd wake her. Wait, what did bookworm mean again? Ah, whatever.[l][r]
"... Stupid Chi-chan."[r]
There was no answer from her despite all the efforts I made to wake her up.[l][r]
No matter how much I shook her, hit her, poked her cheeks, or pinched her nose, she wouldn't open her eyes.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]It was really... sad. We had spent so much time together, it felt like she became my other half, but now...[l][r]
... now, she wasn't moving anymore.[l][r]
A void burrowed its way into my heart, hurting and tearing it apart.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
There was one thing that comforted me, though... Chi-chan slept with a peaceful expression on her face. She looked happy.[r]
Seeing that, I felt really glad to be the one that was next to her in the end.[l][r]
I tentatively reached out to brush a stray strand of hair behind her ear. Thank you for always driving us around.[l][r]
Despite knowing that she couldn't hear me, I kept calling out to her.[l]I wish I could stay asleep like this, too. Chi-chan went ahead without me, and I had to catch up.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]I pulled her into a tight hug and draped the blanket over the two of us. She was so cold to the touch.[l][r]
I hoped I wouldn't wake up, but...[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Huh...?"[l][r]
Suddenly, a drop of water fell on my head, pulling me out of my oncoming slumber.[l][r]
Before I could even come to my senses, the snowfall had been replaced with rain, drops of water plummeting down with rising intensity.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[playse  volume="100"  time="1000"  buf="0"  storage="rain1.ogg"  ]
[bg  time="1000"  method="crossfade"  storage="rain.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
[r]It's raining. How is it <i>raining</i>? There was so much snow just now![l][r]
I pick myself up on instinct as the rain grows harsher, now threatening to soak us both.[r]
I need to get back to the staircase. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I covered Chi-chan with the blanket, scooped her up, and grabbed a few random things before stuffing them into my pockets as I ran off.[l][r]
The fluffy snow had quickly become slushy from the rain, getting into my boots. It was cold and unpleasant.[l][r]
I needed to get back down. Holding Chii-chan so that she doesn't get soaked, I started running, and... that’s when it happened.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

